transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling, this is John, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, hold on please, I've been trying to reach y'all all morning, uh...

Speaker 1: I was promised a delivery yesterday afternoon, and as of yesterday it hasn't come, and today it hasn't come.

Speaker 2: Okay, your name and zip code, sir?

Speaker 1: Uh, my name is Steven, S-T-E-P-H-E-N, my last name is Renfro, R-E-N-F-R-O, and the zip code is 70458.

Speaker 2: Okay, 603 Joseph Street?

Speaker 1: That's me, I actually received an email yesterday that it was sent and had arrived. I don't understand.

Speaker 2: Well, sir, first, we don't control the post office, so this is not in our control, but it does say it's going to be delivered tomorrow.

Speaker 1: My guess is that the weather that's been happening the last few days has slowed this down getting to you.

Speaker 2: It was, uh, arrived in New Orleans today, and it says expect a delivery Wednesday the 28th.

Speaker 1: Okay, I thank you very much. I'm starting to get worried that this was some...

Speaker 2: I was also fixing to call my credit card company and see if it did the process, but I think this is a legit...

Speaker 1: I'm sorry, I'm listening.

Speaker 2: It's definitely legit. I was just going to say, if, let's say, somehow this gets lost and never shows up, we will just reship it to you, so...

Speaker 1: But I expect it to show up tomorrow.

Speaker 2: Alright, I thank you very much. You've been so helpful, and you have a great day.

Speaker 1: You too, sir. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you very much.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
